‚óŹ All CI gates pass. Here's a summary of everything implemented:

  Recommendation 1: Telemetry wired into IO path (FR-011, SC-006)

  - dispatch_command() now measures latency with Instant around sync read/write
  and calls telemetry.record() (feature-gated)
  - Async completions also carry telemetry data back through
  AsyncCompletionEntry

  Recommendation 2: True async IO (FR-004, FR-005, SC-002)

  - ReadAsync/WriteAsync now submit SPDK commands non-blocking via
  async_completion_cb
  - PendingOp entries persist until completion arrives (no longer immediately
  removed)
  - poll_clients() calls process_completions() on all qpairs, then drains the
  completion buffer and routes to clients
  - Abort now works: removes handle from pending_ops; when SPDK completion
  arrives later, it's silently discarded
  - Timeouts now work: check_timeouts() fires correctly since ops are truly
  pending

  Recommendation 3: Write-zeros (FR-006)

  - Added spdk_nvme_ns_cmd_write_zeroes to spdk-sys/build.rs
  - do_write_zeros() uses the native NVMe write-zeroes command (no DMA buffer
  needed)

  Recommendation 4: Auto-detect client disconnect (FR-019)

  - poll_clients() checks for ChannelError::Closed from try_recv()
  - Disconnected clients are silently removed (no error completions sent, per
  spec)
  - DisconnectClient handler also updated to silently discard

  Recommendation 5: Extended spdk-sys bindings (FR-008, FR-009, SC-004)

  - Added bindings: spdk_nvme_ctrlr_create_ns, delete_ns, format, reset, plus
  spdk_nvme_ns_data and spdk_nvme_format types
  - namespace::create/format/delete now call actual SPDK functions
  - ControllerReset handler calls spdk_nvme_ctrlr_reset and refreshes namespaces

  Recommendation 6: Document flush_io() contract

  - Added crate-level docs and connect_client() doc comment explaining the
  flush_io() requirement

